@* Tailwind's surface syntax through the STATIC attribute path (decision 151). Variant colons,
   fraction slashes, arbitrary-value brackets, leading dashes -- and, the defect this witness
   pins: MANY TOKENS in one class value. Razor lowers such a value as SEVERAL prefixed
   HtmlAttributeValue nodes; a concat that reads only the tokens drops the prefixes, welding
   "w-1/2 hover:bg-amber-400 ..." into one garbage class. The emitted string must equal the
   authored string, byte for byte, at top level AND inside a keyed list row. *@

<h1 id="title" class="w-1/2 hover:bg-amber-400 focus:ring-2 max-w-[42rem] sm:px-4 -mt-2 md:grid-cols-[1fr_2fr]">Todo</h1>

<button id="inc" @onclick="Inc" class="bg-cyan-500/75 disabled:opacity-50">inc: <span id="out">@count</span></button>

<ul id="list">@foreach (int i in items)
{
    <li @key="i" class="flex w-1/2 hover:bg-amber-400 max-w-[42rem]"><span>@i</span></li>
}</ul>

@code {
    private int count = 0;
    private List<int> items = new List<int> { 1, 2 };

    void Inc()
    {
        count++;
        items = items.Where(x => true).ToList();
    }
}
